{"key":"post-12994916","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12994916</id>\n<content>If you turn it 90 degrees each day you can make some really cool twisty shrooms!&amp;nbsp; I've done that with Reishi and they damn near tie themselves in a knot.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Light from the sides is actually better since there's four sides and only one top.&amp;nbsp; Mushrooms use light as a source of energy so the more the better.&amp;nbsp; You can leave them to grow towards the window or rotate the terrarium daily.&amp;nbsp; It's your choice.&amp;nbsp; It really won't make much difference.&amp;nbsp; Crooked mushrooms work just as well as straight ones.&amp;nbsp; An alternative is to place a cfl lamp on the side opposite the window so they're getting light from two directions.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12995074</next>\n<prev>12994800</prev>\n<first>12994797</first>\n<last>12995074</last>\n<when>1280847168</when>\n<utime>08/03/10 05:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}